<h2>Do I have a life?</h2>
<p>
Why, yes... yes I do... or did at any rate.  
<p>
Although research is obviously its own reward, I have pursued a truly
ridiculous slew of hobbies over the years.  For example, I sometimes
wrote <I>Hip Hop Reviews</I>; used to run <I>The Annual New Jack Hip
Hop Awards</I>; ran the <I>funky-music</I> and <I>hiphop mailing
lists</I>; and for more than 15 years maintained the <I>This Week In
Black History</I> page and calendar (I believe it was one of the first
online databases of its kind).
<p>
I sometimes interact with the physical world, doing things like
racquetball, reading (I have several thousand more than 20,000 comic
books because, well, of course I do), and ultimate 
frisbee. <!--<a target=_blank href="http://www.isbell.org/">-->I have
a family, too<!--</a>-->, or so they tell me.
